SUPERSPORT United have announced the signing of an attacking midfielder from city rivals Mamelodi Sundowns.Matsatsantsa have secured the services of a 27-year-old Mogakolodi Ngele on a short-term loan deal.The club announced on Friday.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Botswana international has struggled to break into The Brazilians outfit since his return from a loan stay at current Absa Premiership champions Bidvest Wits last season.With in dire need of attacking reinforcements following striker Jeremy Brockie's move to The Brazilians, Eric Tinkler will now look to Ngele to assist up front."Since the departure of Jeremy Brockie to Sundowns, and with Bradley Grobler injured, we need some experience up front to help bring some of our youngsters through," said CEO Stan Matthews in a club statement."The same way Yeye has helped Teboho Mokoena and Sipho Mbule, our hope is that Mogakolodi can be that player, he has an amazing record, winning trophies wherever he goes and making critical contributions in big games."He will be with us for the remainder of the season and, if successful, we will see what we can do to extend his stay.”Matsatsantsa A Pitori also revealed that Reneilwe Letsolonyane and Clayton Daniels have extended their contracts with the club.“Yeye and Clayton have shown tremendous commitment to the club and have been heavily involved in our success over the last few years," said Matthews."Players like them are few & far between both have had long careers & just seem to keep going & going, they both represent the ambitions and vision of the club, with fantastic performances and an eye on the development of younger players."It is a pleasure to reward their efforts with contract extensions."